  "summary": "After a tense conversation in a café, the narrator proposes marriage to Yuzu, explaining that it is the only logical solution because he understands her and possesses what she seeks. Yuzu calmly accepts the proposal.\n\nReturning to a room where Kumozawa is listening to a record, the narrator learns that Detective Jouji is on his way, signaling the potential resolution of the case. Mukai provides a beige business envelope containing a report from Cleo of the Mukimizu Detective Agency regarding McArthur. While the narrator initially wonders if McArthur is a suspect, Mukai clarifies that he is not the killer.\n\nThe group, including Detective Tsujimura and Detective Kuroda, heads toward McArthur's room. Upon entering, they discover a gruesome scene: McArthur has been murdered, and his severed head is resting on a table next to a \"tailless evening gown.\" The victim had been dead for less than an hour.\n\nMukai reveals a significant discovery from the reports: McArthur is actually the son of Matsuri and Rokushu Miyuki, making his real name part of the Dragon Tree Lai family. This connection explains McArthur's intense reaction to the news regarding Yashiro's Tsubaki lineage. The Chief Inspector, Muto, expresses regret for his optimism and his failure to lead the case, noting that he felt forced to listen to his opponent's explanation. As the group follows Muto toward the church, there is a sense that a final, tragic act is unfolding.",
